2	2	# Software Engineering and Analytics Division (SEAD)\n## Information and Communications Laboratory (ICL)\n### Georgia Tech Research Institute (GTRI)\n\nThe **Software Engineering and Analytics Division (SEAD)** is a premier applied research organization within the Georgia Tech Research Institute. We specialize in the design, development, and deployment of complex, mission-critical software systems and advanced data analytics solutions. Our division serves as a bridge between academic innovation and practical, scalable applications for government and industry partners.\n\n---\n\n## Core Competencies & Capabilities\n\nSEAD leverages a multi-disciplinary approach to solve the most pressing challenges in software modernization and data-driven decision-making. Our primary areas of expertise include:\n\n### 1. Full-Stack Software Engineering\n* **Agile Development:** Implementation of Scaled Agile Framework (SAFe) and Scrum methodologies to ensure rapid, iterative delivery of software.\n* **DevSecOps:** Integration of security at every stage of the software development lifecycle, utilizing automated CI/CD pipelines to ensure robust and secure deployments.\n* **Cloud-Native Architectures:** Expertise in AWS, Azure, and private cloud environments, focusing on containerization (Docker, Kubernetes) and serverless computing.\n\n### 2. Advanced Data Analytics & AI\n* **Machine Learning (ML) & Deep Learning:** Development of custom models for predictive analytics, natural language processing (NLP), and computer vision.\n* **Data Engineering:** Designing scalable data lakes and warehouses capable of processing massive datasets (Big Data) for real-time insights.\n* **Decision Support Systems:** Creating intuitive visualizations and dashboards that translate complex data into actionable intelligence for leadership.\n\n### 3. Systems Modernization\n* **Legacy Refactoring:** Modernizing monolithic legacy systems into microservices-based architectures to improve maintainability an